79 void testSOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(void) {
80  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(0u, BMS_CHARGING));
81  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(0u, BMS_DISCHARGING));
82  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(0u, BMS_RELAXATION));
83  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(0u, BMS_AT_REST));
84 
85  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(BS_MAXIMUM_PACK_CURRENT_mA, BMS_CHARGING));
86  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(BS_MAXIMUM_PACK_CURRENT_mA, BMS_DISCHARGING));
87  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(BS_MAXIMUM_PACK_CURRENT_mA, BMS_RELAXATION));
88  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(BS_MAXIMUM_PACK_CURRENT_mA, BMS_AT_REST));
89 
90  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(BS_MAXIMUM_PACK_CURRENT_mA + 1u, BMS_CHARGING));
91  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(BS_MAXIMUM_PACK_CURRENT_mA + 1u, BMS_DISCHARGING));
92  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(BS_MAXIMUM_PACK_CURRENT_mA + 1u, BMS_RELAXATION));
93  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(BS_MAXIMUM_PACK_CURRENT_mA + 1u, BMS_AT_REST));
94 
95  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(UINT32_MAX, BMS_CHARGING));
96  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(UINT32_MAX, BMS_DISCHARGING));
97  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(UINT32_MAX, BMS_RELAXATION));
98  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsPackCurrentLimitViolated(UINT32_MAX, BMS_AT_REST));
99 }

123 void testSOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(void) {
124  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(0u, BMS_CHARGING));
125  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(0u, BMS_DISCHARGING));
126  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(0u, BMS_RELAXATION));
127  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(0u, BMS_AT_REST));
128 
129  uint32_t chargeLimit = BS_NR_OF_PARALLEL_CELLS_PER_MODULE * BC_CURRENT_MAX_CHARGE_MSL_mA;
130  uint32_t dischargeLimit = BS_NR_OF_PARALLEL_CELLS_PER_MODULE * BC_CURRENT_MAX_DISCHARGE_MSL_mA;
131 
132  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(chargeLimit, BMS_CHARGING));
133  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(dischargeLimit, BMS_DISCHARGING));
134  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(chargeLimit, BMS_RELAXATION));
135  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(chargeLimit, BMS_AT_REST));
136  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(dischargeLimit, BMS_RELAXATION));
137  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(dischargeLimit, BMS_AT_REST));
138 
139  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(chargeLimit + 1u, BMS_CHARGING));
140  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(dischargeLimit + 1u, BMS_DISCHARGING));
141  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(chargeLimit + 1u, BMS_RELAXATION));
142  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(chargeLimit + 1u, BMS_AT_REST));
143  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(dischargeLimit + 1u, BMS_RELAXATION));
144  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(dischargeLimit + 1u, BMS_AT_REST));
145 
146  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(UINT32_MAX, BMS_CHARGING));
147  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(UINT32_MAX, BMS_DISCHARGING));
148  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(UINT32_MAX, BMS_RELAXATION));
149  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCellCurrentLimitViolated(UINT32_MAX, BMS_AT_REST));
150 }

152 void testSOA_IsCurrentOnOpenString(void) {
153  BMS_IsStringClosed_ExpectAndReturn(0u, false);
154  BMS_IsStringPrecharging_ExpectAndReturn(0u, false);
155  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, SOA_IsCurrentOnOpenString(BMS_CHARGING, 0u));
156 
157  BMS_IsStringClosed_ExpectAndReturn(0u, true);
158  BMS_IsStringPrecharging_ExpectAndReturn(0u, false);
159  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCurrentOnOpenString(BMS_CHARGING, 0u));
160 
161  BMS_IsStringClosed_ExpectAndReturn(0u, false);
162  BMS_IsStringPrecharging_ExpectAndReturn(0u, true);
163  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, SOA_IsCurrentOnOpenString(BMS_CHARGING, 0u));
164 }
